# Addressing PR Review Comments

When asked to address, fix, or resolve PR comments, follow these steps.

## 1. Identify the PR

Run `git branch --show-current` to get the active branch, then find the open PR:

```bash
gh pr list --head <branch> --repo Modelcode-ai/lens-www --json number,title --limit 1
```

If no PR is found, stop and tell the user.

## 2. Fetch PR Comments

Use `agent-browser` to view the PR comments:

> 1. Open Github `` (or whatever port the dev server is running on — check the terminal).
>    ```bash
>    agent-browser --session-name github open https://github.com/Modelcode-ai/lens-www/pulls
>    ```
>    Look for the pull request and click it. This will load the pull request.

## 3. Triage Comments

- Ignore resolved threads.
- Group remaining comments by file and order them by line number.
- Summarize all unresolved comments to the user before making changes.

## 4. Address Each Comment

For each unresolved comment:
1. Read the referenced file and surrounding context.
2. Make the requested change. If the comment is ambiguous, ask the user for clarification rather than guessing.
3. Follow all project rules (see `frontend.mdc` and `team/` rules) when writing code.

## 5. Report Back

After all changes are made, provide a summary listing:
- Each comment addressed and what was changed.
- Any comments skipped (with reason).
- Any comments that need the user's decision.
